{# For driving school owners #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="for-owners" data-animate="fade-up">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>For driving school owners</h2>
    <p>If you own a driving school and are thinking about your next move, we are open to a quiet, confidential conversation. We acquire established driving schools and help owners step back, exit, or join a larger group, while protecting the brand and instructors they have built.</p>
    <a href="/acquisitions/" class="btn btn--primary">Talk about your driving school</a>
  </div>
</section>

{# For instructors and operators #}
<section class="section section--light" id="for-instructors" data-animate="fade-up">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>For instructors and operators</h2>
    <p>We are building practical services for professional driving instructors and driving school operators. Our first service is Driving Instructor Car Hire, a dual-control vehicle hire service for accredited instructors who need to keep teaching when their own car is off the road. More industry services will follow as the group grows.</p>
    <a href="/industry-services/" class="btn btn--secondary">See industry services</a>
  </div>
</section>

{# For agencies and organisations #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="for-agencies" data-animate="fade-up">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>For agencies and organisations</h2>
    <p>Through our group of driving school brands, we can coordinate lesson delivery for agencies, community organisations, charities, and funded programs that need reliable lessons at scale. One point of contact, multiple instructors, multiple locations.</p>
    <a href="/agencies/" class="btn btn--secondary">Discuss your programme</a>
  </div>
</section>

{# Mission #}
<section class="section section--light" id="mission" data-animate="fade-up">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Our mission</h2>
    <p>We are working to lift standards in driver training and to build a stronger, more sustainable industry for instructors, owners, and the learners they teach. We are building for the long term, not flipping businesses.</p>
  </div>
</section>

